* Parquet Storage
** Columnar Layout
***_ Data stored per column, not per row
***_ Column pruning: read only needed columns
***_ Better compression for similar values
** Row Groups
***_ Data divided into row groups
***_ Each group has column chunks
***_ Column statistics (min/max, null count)
** Optimizations
***_ Column pruning → less I/O
***_ Predicate pushdown → skip row groups
***_ Ideal for analytical workloads
@endmindmap
